grep is used to search for specific text within files. 

It takes two parameters, first what to search for and second which file to search, and then print's the matches it finds.

Can also be used to search for a term inside data that has been inputted to it using |

It is also useful to pass the output to wc (using | ) in order to count the number of files found with the term.

Can also be used with * (wildcards) to search through multiple files.

e.g. grep world hello.rb

e.g. env | grep README | wc -l
